<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98965325115458></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98965325115458><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/item.html?item=3579&mid=98965325115458>THIS AXE ROCKS THE HOUSE!</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=50116><span id= >Hagh</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, May 12th 3:40 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you don't think this weapon is any good, your not thinking.  First off, it doesn't kick in until after 20th level, when the cap on weapon damage is lifted from 33 to the weapon rating.  Then, you use it when pulling, when you whack something once to get its attention then run, and as a first striker.  Learn to switch your weapons!  At 30th at the giant fort in Frontier Mountains I would regularly do 300-500 pt damage pulls because of double strike and riposte.  If you use it at pull, run back and use it as first strike (it takes about that much time for a pull at giants anyway), you can do ABSURD amounts of damage BEFORE your group gets hit once!  At 40th level plus, people still Gasp in awe of the hits it can do.  There is, however, a cap on crit damage. At 41, i did my first crit over 350, before that, the crits did little more than good regular hits.. but when you can hit 3 times for over 200 pts each, WHO CARES.  Get it.  Learn it.  You will LOVE it.)<br>&nbsp;<br>Hagh (43st Warrior)<br>Fleshe Puppett(21st Necromancer)<br>Alek (30th Druid)</td></tr>
