	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is not uncommon for a Warrior with high strength to use this weapon for his initial strike, and then switch to a different weapon with a reasonable delay.  The reason for a high strength score is that this makes it more likely that you hit (STR adds to ATK) and it makes it more likely that you get a nice high damage, which is after all the reason you're doing this.  I have seen nice opening doubles of over 100 each, non-crit.<br><br>I know of one Warrior who also switches to this when he berserks, reasoning that a Crippling Blow with this thing would be unreal (he has gotten around 235 and we doubt that's max).  I don't recommend that personally, as the delay seems to me more likely to kill you than the damage is to save you, but it's something that this weapon can give you if that's what you're after.<br><br>This is obviously less than useful for any Warrior below 20th level, as the damage cap will prevent you from doing nearly as much damage as this thing is capable of dealing out.<br><br>Grygus<br>Shaman of Halas<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
